{"word":"G5568 - ψαλμός - psalmós - psal-mos' - Psalm","slug":"G5568","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ψαλμός</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>psalmós"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>psal-mos'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Psalm"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C8;&#x03B1;&#x03BB;&#x03BC;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03C2; - psalmos</b> - <i>psal-mos'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G5567\">G5567</a>; a set piece of <i>music</i>, that is, a sacred <i>ode</i> (accompanied with the voice, harp or other instrument; a &ldquo;psalm&rdquo;); collectively the book of the <i>Psalms</i>: - psalm. Compare <a href=\"#/G5603\">G5603</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G5567\">G5567</a>"}]}